    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Hosea",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 10,
        "summary": "Israel has plowed wickedness and reaped iniquity\u2014Hosea calls upon Israel to seek the Lord.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Israel is an empty vine, he bringeth forth fruit unto himself: according to the multitude of his fruit he hath increased the altars; according to the goodness of his land they have made goodly images.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Vineyard of the Lord.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jacob 5:32 (1\u201377).",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 12:21 (16\u201321).",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 8:11.",
                        "start": 125,
                        "end": 131
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 9
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Their heart is divided; now shall they be found faulty: he shall break down their altars, he shall spoil their images.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Kgs. 18:21; James 1:8; 3\u00a0Ne. 13:24.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0guilty.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For now they shall say, We have no king, because we feared not the Lord; what then should a king do to us?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "They have spoken words, swearing falsely in making a covenant: thus judgment springeth up as hemlock in the furrows of the field.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 24:5; D&C 104:5 (4\u20135).",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The inhabitants of Samaria shall fear because of the calves of Beth-aven: for the people thereof shall mourn over it, and the priests thereof that rejoiced on it, for the glory thereof, because it is departed from it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Kgs. 12:28.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 142,
                        "end": 146
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "It shall be also carried unto Assyria for a present to king Jareb: Ephraim shall receive shame, and Israel shall be ashamed of his own counsel.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 5:13.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 65
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Shame.",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 94
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 48:13.",
                        "start": 116,
                        "end": 123
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 11:6 (5\u20137).",
                        "start": 135,
                        "end": 142
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As for Samaria, her king is cut off as the foam upon the water.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The high places also of Aven, the sin of Israel, shall be destroyed: the thorn and the thistle shall come up on their altars; and they shall say to the mountains, Cover us; and to the hills, Fall on us.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 4:15.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 23:30 (26\u201333); Rev. 6:16 (14\u201317); 2\u00a0Ne. 26:5; Alma 12:14.",
                        "start": 152,
                        "end": 161
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "O Israel, thou hast sinned from the days of Gibeah: there they stood: the battle in Gibeah against the children of iniquity did not overtake them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Judg. 20:4 (1\u201348).",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 9:9.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 50
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Judg. 20:19 (18\u201321).",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "It is in my desire that I should chastise them; and the people shall be gathered against them, when they shall bind themselves in their two furrows.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And Ephraim is as an heifer that is taught, and loveth to tread out the corn; but I passed over upon her fair neck: I will make Ephraim to ride; Judah shall plow, and Jacob shall break his clods.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 163,
                        "end": 166
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Sow to yourselves in righteousness, reap in mercy; break up your fallow ground: for it is time to seek the Lord, till he come and rain righteousness upon you.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Righteousness.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Harvest.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 4:3.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye have plowed wickedness, ye have reaped iniquity; ye have eaten the fruit of lies: because thou didst trust in thy way, in the multitude of thy mighty men.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Wickedness.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore shall a tumult arise among thy people, and all thy fortresses shall be spoiled, as Shalman spoiled Beth-arbel in the day of battle: the mother was dashed in pieces upon her children.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Kgs. 17:3.",
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 100
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 13:16 (15\u201316).",
                        "start": 157,
                        "end": 163
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 179,
                        "end": 182
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "So shall Beth-el do unto you because of your great wickedness: in a morning shall the king of Israel utterly be cut off.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}